{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_120","type":"command_execution","command":"/bin/bash -lc \"nl -ba docs/hybrid_morphology_design.md | sed -n '120,240p'\"","aggregated_output":"   120\t- skeleton -> skeleton\n   121\t- skeleton -> surface\n   122\t- surface -> point\n   123\t- surface -> skeleton\n   124\t- surface -> surface\n   125\t\n   126\tFor every route, the source class supplies the presynaptic readout surface and\n   127\toutgoing anchor resolution, while the target class supplies the landing surface\n   128\tand incoming anchor resolution. The route may change spatial support, but it\n   129\tmay not change Milestone 7 sign, delay, or aggregation semantics.\n   130\t\n   131\t## Promotion And Demotion Invariants\n   132\t\n   133\tPromoting `point_neuron -> skeleton_neuron -> surface_neuron`, or demoting in\n   134\tthe opposite direction, must preserve these meanings unless the contract version\n   135\tchanges:\n   136\t\n   137\t- selected root IDs and manifest-arm identity stay fixed\n   138\t- the selected connectome edge set stays fixed\n   139\t- shared readout IDs, units, and timebase stay fixed\n   140\t- coupling sign, delay, and aggregation semantics stay fixed\n   141\t- root-local input identity and comparison-readout meaning stay fixed\n   142\t- class-specific diagnostics may expand under `extensions/`, but shared result\n   143\t  payloads do not change shape or semantics\n   144\t\n   145\tPromotion is therefore allowed to refine intraneuron state resolution and local\n   146\tspatial patterning. It is not allowed to introduce a new decoder, new edges,\n   147\tnew per-synapse sign rules, or a new top-level model mode.\n   148\t\n   149\t## Policy Hook\n   150\t\n   151\tMilestone 11 now exposes one narrow planner-owned policy hook under\n   152\t`simulation.mixed_fidelity.assignment_policy`. The hook is deterministic and\n   153\treview-oriented: it does not silently rewrite the realized fidelity assignment.\n   154\tInstead, it records what a downstream planner or reviewer should consider\n   155\tpromoting or demoting before relying on a mixed-fidelity arm for later readout\n   156\tor validation work.\n   157\t\n   158\tSupported fields:\n   159\t\n   160\t- `default_source`\n   161\t- `promotion_mode`\n   162\t- `demotion_mode`\n   163\t- `recommendation_rules`\n   164\t\n   165\t`promotion_mode` and `demotion_mode` currently support:\n   166\t\n   167\t- `disabled`\n   168\t- `recommend_from_policy`\n   169\t\n   170\tEach `recommendation_rules[]` entry may declare:\n   171\t\n   172\t- `minimum_morphology_class` and/or `maximum_morphology_class`\n   173\t- optional `root_ids` or `cell_types` filters\n   174\t- optional manifest-context filters:\n   175\t  `topology_conditions`, `morphology_conditions`, `arm_tags_any`\n   176\t- optional numeric descriptor thresholds under `descriptor_thresholds`\n   177\t\n   178\tExample:\n   179\t\n   180\t```yaml\n   181\tsimulation:\n   182\t  mixed_fidelity:\n   183\t    assignment_policy:\n   184\t      promotion_mode: recommend_from_policy\n   185\t      demotion_mode: disabled\n   186\t      recommendation_rules:\n   187\t        - rule_id: promote_patch_dense_surrogate\n   188\t          minimum_morphology_class: surface_neuron\n   189\t          root_ids: [303]\n   190\t          topology_conditions: [intact]\n   191\t          arm_tags_any: [surface_wave]\n   192\t          descriptor_thresholds:\n   193\t            patch_count:\n   194\t              gte: 2\n   195\t```\n   196\t\n   197\tThe normalized mixed-fidelity plan records, for each root:\n   198\t\n   199\t- the realized morphology class\n   200\t- the recommended morphology class\n   201\t- whether that recommendation implies promotion, demotion, or no change\n   202\t- which policy rules matched\n   203\t- the descriptor and manifest context used for that decision\n   204\t\n   205\tThe planner summary also includes a `policy_hook` block that lists all rule IDs\n   206\tand the roots currently flagged for promotion or demotion review.\n   207\t\n   208\t## Serialization Rules\n   209\t\n   210\tEvery per-root class record must remain deterministic and include at least:\n   211\t\n   212\t- `root_id`\n   213\t- `morphology_class`\n   214\t- `source_project_role`\n   215\t- `promotion_rank`\n   216\t\n   217\tThe normalized contract payload is serialized in three places:\n   218\t\n   219\t- `surface_wave_execution_plan.hybrid_morphology`\n   220\t- `execution_provenance.json -> model_execution.hybrid_morphology`\n   221\t- `surface_wave_summary.json -> hybrid_morphology`\n   222\t\n   223\tShared comparison traces still live in `simulator_result_bundle.v1`. Class-\n   224\tspecific state or diagnostics may live under `extensions/`, but they may not\n   225\tmutate the shared readout catalog, shared trace layout, or shared metric table.\n   226\t\n   227\t## Scope Boundary\n   228\t\n   229\tThis note freezes the vocabulary for mixed morphology classes, approximation\n   230\tlimits, and promotion invariants. Later Milestone 11 tickets may implement more\n   231\tof the runtime, but they should cite this note instead of inventing new class\n   232\tnames or changing what `point_neuron`, `skeleton_neuron`, or `surface_neuron`\n   233\tmean inside one simulator run.\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
