{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_136","type":"command_execution","command":"/bin/bash -lc \"nl -ba docs/hybrid_morphology_design.md | sed -n '149,240p'\"","aggregated_output":"   149\t## Policy Hook\n   150\t\n   151\tMilestone 11 now exposes one narrow planner-owned policy hook under\n   152\t`simulation.mixed_fidelity.assignment_policy`. The hook is deterministic and\n   153\treview-oriented: it does not silently rewrite the realized fidelity assignment.\n   154\tInstead, it records what a downstream planner or reviewer should consider\n   155\tpromoting or demoting before relying on a mixed-fidelity arm for later readout\n   156\tor validation work.\n   157\t\n   158\tSupported fields:\n   159\t\n   160\t- `default_source`\n   161\t- `promotion_mode`\n   162\t- `demotion_mode`\n   163\t- `recommendation_rules`\n   164\t\n   165\t`promotion_mode` and `demotion_mode` currently support:\n   166\t\n   167\t- `disabled`\n   168\t- `recommend_from_policy`\n   169\t\n   170\tEach `recommendation_rules[]` entry may declare:\n   171\t\n   172\t- `minimum_morphology_class` and/or `maximum_morphology_class`\n   173\t- optional `root_ids` or `cell_types` filters\n   174\t- optional manifest-context filters:\n   175\t  `topology_conditions`, `morphology_conditions`, `arm_tags_any`\n   176\t- optional numeric descriptor thresholds under `descriptor_thresholds`\n   177\t\n   178\tExample:\n   179\t\n   180\t```yaml\n   181\tsimulation:\n   182\t  mixed_fidelity:\n   183\t    assignment_policy:\n   184\t      promotion_mode: recommend_from_policy\n   185\t      demotion_mode: disabled\n   186\t      recommendation_rules:\n   187\t        - rule_id: promote_patch_dense_surrogate\n   188\t          minimum_morphology_class: surface_neuron\n   189\t          root_ids: [303]\n   190\t          topology_conditions: [intact]\n   191\t          arm_tags_any: [surface_wave]\n   192\t          descriptor_thresholds:\n   193\t            patch_count:\n   194\t              gte: 2\n   195\t```\n   196\t\n   197\tThe normalized mixed-fidelity plan records, for each root:\n   198\t\n   199\t- the realized morphology class\n   200\t- the recommended morphology class\n   201\t- whether that recommendation implies promotion, demotion, or no change\n   202\t- which policy rules matched\n   203\t- the descriptor and manifest context used for that decision\n   204\t\n   205\tThe planner summary also includes a `policy_hook` block that lists all rule IDs\n   206\tand the roots currently flagged for promotion or demotion review.\n   207\t\n   208\t## Serialization Rules\n   209\t\n   210\tEvery per-root class record must remain deterministic and include at least:\n   211\t\n   212\t- `root_id`\n   213\t- `morphology_class`\n   214\t- `source_project_role`\n   215\t- `promotion_rank`\n   216\t\n   217\tThe normalized contract payload is serialized in three places:\n   218\t\n   219\t- `surface_wave_execution_plan.hybrid_morphology`\n   220\t- `execution_provenance.json -> model_execution.hybrid_morphology`\n   221\t- `surface_wave_summary.json -> hybrid_morphology`\n   222\t\n   223\tShared comparison traces still live in `simulator_result_bundle.v1`. Class-\n   224\tspecific state or diagnostics may live under `extensions/`, but they may not\n   225\tmutate the shared readout catalog, shared trace layout, or shared metric table.\n   226\t\n   227\t## Scope Boundary\n   228\t\n   229\tThis note freezes the vocabulary for mixed morphology classes, approximation\n   230\tlimits, and promotion invariants. Later Milestone 11 tickets may implement more\n   231\tof the runtime, but they should cite this note instead of inventing new class\n   232\tnames or changing what `point_neuron`, `skeleton_neuron`, or `surface_neuron`\n   233\tmean inside one simulator run.\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_135","type":"command_execution","command":"/bin/bash -lc \"nl -ba src/flywire_wave/config.py | sed -n '1,80p'\"","aggregated_output":"     1\tfrom __future__ import annotations\n     2\t\n     3\tfrom pathlib import Path\n     4\tfrom typing import Any\n     5\t\n     6\timport yaml\n     7\t\n     8\tfrom .retinal_geometry import has_retinal_geometry_reference, resolve_retinal_geometry_spec\n     9\tfrom .stimulus_registry import has_stimulus_reference, resolve_stimulus_spec\n    10\t\n    11\t\n    12\tREPO_ROOT = Path(__file__).resolve().parents[2]\n    13\tCONFIG_METADATA_KEY = \"__config_metadata__\"\n    14\tDEFAULT_PATHS = {\n    15\t    \"codex_raw_dir\": Path(\"data/raw/codex\"),\n    16\t    \"neuron_registry_csv\": Path(\"data/interim/registry/neuron_registry.csv\"),\n    17\t    \"connectivity_registry_csv\": Path(\"data/interim/registry/connectivity_registry.csv\"),\n    18\t    \"registry_provenance_json\": Path(\"data/interim/registry/registry_provenance.json\"),\n    19\t    \"selected_root_ids\": Path(\"data/interim/root_ids_visual_sample.txt\"),\n    20\t    \"subset_output_dir\": Path(\"data/interim/subsets\"),\n    21\t    \"meshes_raw_dir\": Path(\"data/interim/meshes_raw\"),\n    22\t    \"skeletons_raw_dir\": Path(\"data/interim/skeletons_raw\"),\n    23\t    \"processed_mesh_dir\": Path(\"data/processed/meshes\"),\n    24\t    \"processed_graph_dir\": Path(\"data/processed/graphs\"),\n    25\t    \"processed_coupling_dir\": Path(\"data/processed/coupling\"),\n    26\t    \"coupling_inspection_dir\": Path(\"data/processed/coupling_inspection\"),\n    27\t    \"geometry_preview_dir\": Path(\"data/processed/previews\"),\n    28\t    \"operator_qa_dir\": Path(\"data/processed/operator_qa\"),\n    29\t    \"processed_stimulus_dir\": Path(\"data/processed/stimuli\"),\n    30\t    \"processed_retinal_dir\": Path(\"data/processed/retinal\"),\n    31\t    \"processed_simulator_results_dir\": Path(\"data/processed/simulator_results\"),\n    32\t    \"surface_wave_inspection_dir\": Path(\"data/processed/surface_wave_inspection\"),\n    33\t    \"mixed_fidelity_inspection_dir\": Path(\"data/processed/mixed_fidelity_inspection\"),\n    34\t    \"manifest_json\": Path(\"data/processed/asset_manifest.json\"),\n    35\t}\n    36\t\n    37\t\n    38\tdef load_config(path: str | Path, *, project_root: str | Path | None = None) -> dict[str, Any]:\n    39\t    cfg_path = _resolve_input_path(path)\n    40\t    with cfg_path.open(\"r\", encoding=\"utf-8\") as f:\n    41\t        cfg = yaml.safe_load(f)\n    42\t    if not isinstance(cfg, dict):\n    43\t        raise ValueError(f\"Config at {cfg_path} is not a mapping.\")\n    44\t\n    45\t    resolved_project_root = _resolve_project_root(project_root)\n    46\t    resolved_paths = _resolve_paths_mapping(cfg.get(\"paths\"), project_root=resolved_project_root)\n    47\t\n    48\t    loaded_cfg = dict(cfg)\n    49\t    loaded_cfg[\"paths\"] = resolved_paths\n    50\t    loaded_cfg[CONFIG_METADATA_KEY] = {\n    51\t        \"config_path\": str(cfg_path),\n    52\t        \"project_root\": str(resolved_project_root),\n    53\t    }\n    54\t    if has_stimulus_reference(loaded_cfg):\n    55\t        resolved_stimulus = resolve_stimulus_spec(loaded_cfg)\n    56\t        processed_stimulus_dir = resolved_paths[\"processed_stimulus_dir\"]\n    57\t        loaded_cfg[\"stimulus\"] = resolved_stimulus.stimulus_spec\n    58\t        loaded_cfg[\"stimulus_registry_entry\"] = resolved_stimulus.registry_entry\n    59\t        loaded_cfg[\"stimulus_contract\"] = resolved_stimulus.build_contract_metadata(\n    60\t            processed_stimulus_dir=processed_stimulus_dir\n    61\t        )\n    62\t        loaded_cfg[\"stimulus_bundle\"] = resolved_stimulus.build_bundle_metadata(\n    63\t            processed_stimulus_dir=processed_stimulus_dir\n    64\t        )\n    65\t        loaded_cfg[\"stimulus_bundle_reference\"] = resolved_stimulus.build_bundle_reference(\n    66\t            processed_stimulus_dir=processed_stimulus_dir\n    67\t        )\n    68\t        loaded_cfg[\"stimulus_bundle_metadata_path\"] = resolved_stimulus.resolve_bundle_metadata_path(\n    69\t            processed_stimulus_dir=processed_stimulus_dir\n    70\t        )\n    71\t    if has_retinal_geometry_reference(loaded_cfg):\n    72\t        resolved_retinal_geometry = resolve_retinal_geometry_spec(loaded_cfg)\n    73\t        loaded_cfg[\"retinal_geometry\"] = resolved_retinal_geometry.retinal_geometry\n    74\t        loaded_cfg[\"retinal_geometry_registry_entry\"] = resolved_retinal_geometry.registry_entry\n    75\t    return loaded_cfg\n    76\t\n    77\t\n    78\tdef get_config_path(cfg: dict[str, Any]) -> Path | None:\n    79\t    metadata = cfg.get(CONFIG_METADATA_KEY, {})\n    80\t    config_path = metadata.get(\"config_path\")\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_138","type":"command_execution","command":"/bin/bash -lc \"nl -ba docs/mixed_fidelity_inspection.md | sed -n '1,220p'\"","aggregated_output":"     1\t# Mixed-Fidelity Inspection Workflow\n     2\t\n     3\tMilestone 11 is not finished when surface, skeleton, and point classes merely\n     4\trun in one arm. Reviewers need one offline workflow that can answer:\n     5\t\n     6\t- which roots were assigned to which fidelity class\n     7\t- what the policy hook recommended promoting or demoting\n     8\t- how a lower-fidelity surrogate behaves against a declared higher-fidelity\n     9\t  reference on the same local fixture\n    10\t- whether the observed deviations are acceptable, review-level, or blocking\n    11\t- which roots should be promoted before later readout or validation work relies\n    12\t  on them\n    13\t\n    14\t`scripts/18_mixed_fidelity_inspection.py` is that workflow.\n    15\t\n    16\t## Inputs\n    17\t\n    18\tThe workflow consumes only local artifacts:\n    19\t\n    20\t- one manifest with at least one `surface_wave` arm\n    21\t- the local geometry, operator, skeleton, and coupling assets already referenced\n    22\t  by that arm\n    23\t- a recorded local stimulus bundle compatible with the manifest timing\n    24\t- the normalized mixed-fidelity policy inside `simulation.mixed_fidelity`\n    25\t\n    26\tNo live FlyWire access is required.\n    27\t\n    28\t## Run It\n    29\t\n    30\tInspect the shipped `surface_wave` arm and let the resolved policy choose which\n    31\tsurrogate roots to compare against a higher-fidelity reference:\n    32\t\n    33\t```bash\n    34\tpython scripts/18_mixed_fidelity_inspection.py \\\n    35\t  --config config/local.yaml \\\n    36\t  --manifest manifests/examples/milestone_1_demo.yaml \\\n    37\t  --schema schemas/milestone_1_experiment_manifest.schema.json \\\n    38\t  --design-lock config/milestone_1_design_lock.yaml \\\n    39\t  --arm-id surface_wave_intact\n    40\t```\n    41\t\n    42\tProvide explicit reference roots when you want to override the policy target:\n    43\t\n    44\t```bash\n    45\tpython scripts/18_mixed_fidelity_inspection.py \\\n    46\t  --config config/local.yaml \\\n    47\t  --manifest manifests/examples/milestone_1_demo.yaml \\\n    48\t  --schema schemas/milestone_1_experiment_manifest.schema.json \\\n    49\t  --design-lock config/milestone_1_design_lock.yaml \\\n    50\t  --arm-id surface_wave_intact \\\n    51\t  --reference-root 303:surface_neuron\n    52\t```\n    53\t\n    54\tEquivalent Make target:\n    55\t\n    56\t```bash\n    57\tmake mixed-fidelity-inspect \\\n    58\t  CONFIG=config/local.yaml \\\n    59\t  MIXED_FIDELITY_INSPECT_ARGS=\"--arm-id surface_wave_intact --reference-root 303:surface_neuron\"\n    60\t```\n    61\t\n    62\tWhen `--reference-root` is omitted, the workflow first uses any policy-driven\n    63\tpromotion recommendation. If the policy does not nominate a higher-fidelity\n    64\treference, it falls back to the next higher class in the promotion order.\n    65\t\n    66\t## Output Layout\n    67\t\n    68\tThe default output directory is deterministic for the exact arm, normalized\n    69\treference-root set, and normalized thresholds:\n    70\t\n    71\t```text\n    72\tconfig.paths.mixed_fidelity_inspection_dir/experiment-<experiment-id>__arm-<arm-id>__inspection-<hash>/\n    73\t```\n    74\t\n    75\tExample contents:\n    76\t\n    77\t```text\n    78\tdata/processed/mixed_fidelity_inspection/experiment-milestone-1-demo-motion-patch__arm-surface-wave-intact__inspection-<hash>/summary.json\n    79\tdata/processed/mixed_fidelity_inspection/experiment-milestone-1-demo-motion-patch__arm-surface-wave-intact__inspection-<hash>/report.md\n    80\tdata/processed/mixed_fidelity_inspection/experiment-milestone-1-demo-motion-patch__arm-surface-wave-intact__inspection-<hash>/roots.csv\n    81\tdata/processed/mixed_fidelity_inspection/experiment-milestone-1-demo-motion-patch__arm-surface-wave-intact__inspection-<hash>/details/root_303__point_neuron__to__surface_neuron.json\n    82\t```\n    83\t\n    84\t## What It Records\n    85\t\n    86\tThe top-level summary records:\n    87\t\n    88\t- the resolved mixed-fidelity plan excerpt, including per-root fidelity choice\n    89\t  and the normalized policy hook\n    90\t- the base mixed-fidelity run used as the surrogate under review\n    91\t- one reference run per inspected root, built by rewriting only that root's\n    92\t  fidelity assignment in a deterministic manifest sidecar\n    93\t- per-root surrogate-versus-reference metrics:\n    94\t  - root mean-trace MAE\n    95\t  - root peak-amplitude error\n    96\t  - root final-state error\n    97\t  - root peak-timing delta\n    98\t  - shared-output trace MAE\n    99\t  - shared-output peak error\n   100\t- per-check `pass`, `review`, `blocking`, or `blocked` outcomes\n   101\t- the final promotion target list inferred from those deviations\n   102\t\n   103\t## Review Guidance\n   104\t\n   105\t- `pass`: the lower-fidelity surrogate stayed close enough to the declared\n   106\t  reference on the current fixture\n   107\t- `review`: the surrogate diverged enough that a human should decide whether the\n   108\t  approximation is still scientifically defensible\n   109\t- `blocking`: the surrogate materially changed a blocking metric, usually one of\n   110\t  the shared-output comparisons\n   111\t- `blocked`: the workflow could not build or compare the reference variant from\n   112\t  local artifacts, so the root remains unresolved\n   113\t\n   114\tThe workflow is intentionally an approximation audit, not a final biological\n   115\tvalidation ladder. Its job is to keep Milestone 11 honest and produce a stable\n   116\treview artifact for later milestones.\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_137","type":"command_execution","command":"/bin/bash -lc \"nl -ba tests/test_mixed_fidelity_inspection.py | sed -n '1,260p'\"","aggregated_output":"     1\tfrom __future__ import annotations\n     2\t\n     3\timport json\n     4\timport sys\n     5\timport tempfile\n     6\timport unittest\n     7\tfrom pathlib import Path\n     8\t\n     9\timport yaml\n    10\t\n    11\tROOT = Path(__file__).resolve().parents[1]\n    12\tSRC = ROOT / \"src\"\n    13\tsys.path.insert(0, str(SRC))\n    14\tsys.path.insert(0, str(ROOT / \"tests\"))\n    15\t\n    16\tfrom flywire_wave.hybrid_morphology_contract import (\n    17\t    POINT_NEURON_CLASS,\n    18\t    SURFACE_NEURON_CLASS,\n    19\t)\n    20\tfrom flywire_wave.io_utils import write_json\n    21\tfrom flywire_wave.mixed_fidelity_inspection import (\n    22\t    build_mixed_fidelity_inspection_output_dir,\n    23\t    execute_mixed_fidelity_inspection_workflow,\n    24\t)\n    25\tfrom flywire_wave.simulation_planning import resolve_manifest_mixed_fidelity_plan\n    26\tfrom flywire_wave.stimulus_bundle import record_stimulus_bundle, resolve_stimulus_input\n    27\tfrom test_simulation_planning import (\n    28\t    _write_manifest_fixture,\n    29\t    _write_simulation_fixture,\n    30\t)\n    31\t\n    32\t\n    33\tclass MixedFidelityInspectionTest(unittest.TestCase):\n    34\t    def test_mixed_fidelity_policy_normalization_is_deterministic_and_records_recommendations(self) -> None:\n    35\t        with tempfile.TemporaryDirectory(dir=ROOT) as tmp_dir_str:\n    36\t            fixture = _materialize_policy_fixture(Path(tmp_dir_str))\n    37\t\n    38\t            first = resolve_manifest_mixed_fidelity_plan(\n    39\t                manifest_path=fixture[\"manifest_path\"],\n    40\t                config_path=fixture[\"config_path\"],\n    41\t                schema_path=fixture[\"schema_path\"],\n    42\t                design_lock_path=fixture[\"design_lock_path\"],\n 