{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_146","type":"agent_message","text":"**Changes**\n- Added a deterministic mixed-fidelity policy surface in [mixed_fidelity_policy.py](/home/jack/Documents/github/personal/fly_neural_simulation/flywire_wave_repo/src/flywire_wave/mixed_fidelity_policy.py#L18). It normalizes `simulation.mixed_fidelity.assignment_policy`, evaluates per-root promotion/demotion recommendations from descriptor thresholds plus manifest context, and produces a planner-consumable `policy_hook` summary at [mixed_fidelity_policy.py](/home/jack/Documents/github/personal/fly_neural_simulation/flywire_wave_repo/src/flywire_wave/mixed_fidelity_policy.py#L358).\n- Wired that policy into mixed-fidelity planning in [simulation_planning.py](/home/jack/Documents/github/personal/fly_neural_simulation/flywire_wave_repo/src/flywire_wave/simulation_planning.py#L743) and [simulation_planning.py](/home/jack/Documents/github/personal/fly_neural_simulation/flywire_wave_repo/src/flywire_wave/simulation_planning.py#L2123), so each root now carries `policy_evaluation`, provenance records the recommendation, approximation routing records the policy action, and the top-level plan exports `policy_hook`.\n- Added the offline surrogate audit workflow in [mixed_fidelity_inspection.py](/home/jack/Documents/github/personal/fly_neural_simulation/flywire_wave_repo/src/flywire_wave/mixed_fidelity_inspection.py#L205) and [mixed_fidelity_inspection.py](/home/jack/Documents/github/personal/fly_neural_simulation/flywire_wave_repo/src/flywire_wave/mixed_fidelity_inspection.py#L236). It runs local-only mixed-fidelity vs reference comparisons, writes deterministic `summary.json` / `report.md` / `roots.csv` / per-root detail JSON, records per-root fidelity choice, metrics, blocking vs review deviations, and recommended promotion targets. CLI and repo entry points are in [18_mixed_fidelity_inspection.py](/home/jack/Documents/github/personal/fly_neural_simulation/flywire_wave_repo/scripts/18_mixed_fidelity_inspection.py#L19) and [Makefile](/home/jack/Documents/github/personal/fly_neural_simulation/flywire_wave_repo/Makefile#L82); default output path support is in [config.py](/home/jack/Documents/github/personal/fly_neural_simulation/flywire_wave_repo/src/flywire_wave/config.py#L14). Docs were updated in [hybrid_morphology_design.md](/home/jack/Documents/github/personal/fly_neural_simulation/flywire_wave_repo/docs/hybrid_morphology_design.md#L149) and [mixed_fidelity_inspection.md](/home/jack/Documents/github/personal/fly_neural_simulation/flywire_wave_repo/docs/mixed_fidelity_inspection.md#L1).\n\n**Verified**\n- Added deterministic coverage in [test_mixed_fidelity_inspection.py](/home/jack/Documents/github/personal/fly_neural_simulation/flywire_wave_repo/tests/test_mixed_fidelity_inspection.py#L33) and [test_mixed_fidelity_inspection.py](/home/jack/Documents/github/personal/fly_neural_simulation/flywire_wave_repo/tests/test_mixed_fidelity_inspection.py#L91). The fixture case asserts stable policy normalization, deterministic inspection output paths and contents, and a surrogate case where root `303` is flagged for review and recommended for promotion.\n- Ran `make test` successfully. Full suite passed: `146` tests.\n- Also ran targeted validation with `python -m unittest tests.test_mixed_fidelity_inspection -v` and related mixed-fidelity planning tests during implementation."}}
